HEADWORD: Foundling
<hw>Found"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>foundling</ets>, <ets>fundling</ets>; <ets>finden</ets> to find +
<ets>-ling</ets>; cf. <ets>f⟦uum⟧ndling</ets>, <ets>findling</ets>. See
<er>Find</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>, and <er>-ling</er>.]</ety> <def>A
deserted or exposed infant; a child found without a parent or
owner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Foundling hospital</b></col>, <cd>a hospital for
